Global investors  sold a  net 5.54
billion rupees ($100.2 million) of Indian equity  derivatives 
yesterday, according to the National Stock Exchange.  Open interest, or the number of contracts outstanding in
value terms, rose 0.5 percent to 1.007 trillion rupees,
according to the exchangeâ€™s  website . Open interest reached a
record 1.6 trillion rupees on Sept. 21, 2010.  Foreign funds bought a net 2 billion rupees of shares in
the  cash  segment yesterday, according to preliminary data given
